+{"id": "bd-sh-1", "title": "PORT: shadow sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::pwd::shadow parser", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-sh-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-24T10:14:42.768220Z", "description": "Extend crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pwd/shadow.rs with: ShadowEntry { name: Vec<u8>, passwd: Vec<u8>, lstchg, min, max, warn, inact, expire: i64, flag: u64 }; parse_shadow_numeric(s: &[u8]) -> i64 (-1 sentinel for empty/non-numeric, matching glibc); parse_shadow_line(line: &[u8]) -> Option<ShadowEntry> (8+ colon fields, blank/comment skip); lookup_shadow_by_name(content, name) (case-sensitive, matches /etc/shadow lookup semantics). Comprehensive tests covering: typical line, all-sentinel-empty fields, missing optional flag, comment/blank skip, fewer than 8 fields rejected, parse-then-format round-trip with the existing format_shadow_line."}
+{"id": "bd-sh-2", "title": "PORT: shadow sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-sh-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-24T10:14:42.768220Z", "description": "Drop parse_shadow_field + fill_shadow_entry from pwd_abi.rs. Drop the inline parsers from unistd_abi.rs::fgetspent / fgetspent_r. Each caller now: (1) calls core::pwd::shadow::parse_shadow_line; (2) packs name+passwd into the caller buffer with NULs; (3) writes the seven numeric fields directly from ShadowEntry. Verify any shadow-related abi tests still pass."}
+{"id": "bd-sh-1", "title": "PORT: shadow sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::pwd::shadow parser", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-sh-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z", "resolution": "Extended crates/frankenlibc-core/src/pwd/shadow.rs (which already had format_shadow_line from bd-pgs) with: pub struct ShadowEntry (name, passwd: Vec<u8>; lstchg/min/max/warn/inact/expire: i64; flag: u64); parse_shadow_numeric(s: &[u8]) -> i64 returning -1 sentinel for empty/non-numeric; parse_shadow_line(line) -> Option<ShadowEntry> with EOL strip + comment/blank skip + 8-field minimum; lookup_shadow_by_name (case-sensitive per POSIX login-name semantics). Importantly: the missing/empty 9th flag field decodes to u64::MAX (matching glibc ~0UL convention) so parse->format identity is preserved for both -1 and u64::MAX sentinels. 27 tests cover all field shapes including round-trip property tests against format_shadow_line."}
+{"id": "bd-sh-2", "title": "PORT: shadow sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi shims", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-sh-epic", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T10:19:48.660063Z", "resolution": "Removed parse_shadow_field from pwd_abi.rs (~7 lines) and the ~36-line inline parse+pack body in unistd_abi.rs::fgetspent and again in fgetspent_r. Refactored fill_shadow_entry to delegate to core::pwd::shadow::parse_shadow_line + pack name/passwd into TLS buffer. Added fill_shadow_entry_caller helper for the reentrant variants \u2014 getspnam_r and getspent_r each shrink from ~40 lines to ~10 (single core call + result wiring). The C-ABI SpwdEntry layout-stable struct stays in abi. Side-effect correctness fix: empty 9th flag field now decodes to ~0UL per glibc, so parse(format(x)) == x for the sentinel cases. 42/42 pwd_abi tests, 178/178 unistd_abi tests, 173/173 abi lib tests all pass."}
